Ok, finally I see your point. Now I understand the `directory` sugestion.

My comments:

+ the building in FoBiS is not implicit; on the contrary it rely on the depency cascade that the programmer explicitely define... by means `use module...`; the *magic* (forgive me...) of FoBiS is that the programmer has to define two times (one in the fortran sources and the other into the makefile) this dependency;

+ the above is not true gor old fashioned, non-module-library with a blob of procedures; in this case there is not a dependency neither it can easy *argued* if the library has been actually used (I will need to parse sources for also procedures invocations... it is in my plan but not in the next months); as a consequence, these sources are compiked and passed to linker, but it the same thing that it is commonly done with makefile by the (ab)use of wildcards and implicit compiling rules (these are really implicit);

Pointed out the above comments, my feel is that you are right: it can be desiderable (in some scenario) to give the user more control (other than the exclude option). I am thinking to a new option like `only = ['dir1`,'dir1/dir2`,'dir3'...]` where the user specify the only dirs to be considered with recursive search disable. If you like this, please open a new issue with a feature request (not necessarally exact this, but not too far...)

Thank you again, see you soon

