@tjprescott, that's strange. When I hardcode comp_wordbreaks in the code to be empty, my raw (unquoted) completions don't get escaped. Are you sure the code you modify is what gets loaded?

The showstopper problem is that not escaping `=` breaks unquoted completions because bash splits words on `=` and mangles the resulting command line state (repeating the portion before the `=`). There might be a way around this by changing `COMP_WORDBREAKS` in the shell before calling the completion script, but from what I know, that leaks unacceptable side effects into the shell's global state.

I believe there is nothing I can do about this. If you can find a solution, please feel free to submit a patch.

