@kyuupichan this breaks older Coinomi clients that also use the electrum protocol. The reason is a bug incorrectly incorrectly parses `"error":null` as `"error":"null"` and the client assumes that an error occurred.

This was the behavior of the vanilla electrum server (no error variable if no error) and in electrumx until the 06c8eda161a2ae6795bacea92e26977a9c37bd79 commit.

The JSONRPCv1 indeed requires `"error":null`. Is there a way to force the backwards compatible behavior?

