@nburbank Howdy, in this particular test I had to use beforeAll and afterAll to do some data setup, and I kept getting an NPE for `spark` or `sc` when I tried to switch to SharedSparkContext. But when I added the call to super.beforeAll(), it initialized `spark` (or `sc`, depending). So:
```
import com.holdenkarau.spark.testing.DataFrameSuiteBase
import org.scalatest.{BeforeAndAfterAll, FlatSpec, Matchers}

class ConfigFileTest extends FlatSpec with Matchers with BeforeAndAfterAll with DataFrameSuiteBase {

  override def beforeAll(): Unit = {
    super.beforeAll()
    // and then setup my data and stuff
  }
  override def afterAll(): Unit = {
    // teardown my own stuff
    super.afterAll()
  }

  "And now, because I made the call to the super funcs, my SparkSession" should "not be null" in {
    spark shouldNot be null
  }
```

