@KiranPrajapati345  Hi! What are you trying to achieve? Do you want to use DRF-Mongoengine in your project or do you want to contribute to DRF-Mongoengine?

If you want to use DRF-ME in your project, just say `pip install django-rest-framework-mongoengine` and you need all the dependencies from our requirements.txt installed (`django`, `mongoengine`, `drf` and `blinker`) - this can be done with `pip install -r requirements.txt`. Then you can use `DocumentSerializers` from it in your `serializers.py` and `Router` in `urls.py`. 

If you want to contribute to DRF-ME, you just clone DRF-ME from github and then install testing  requirements from `requirements/requirements-testing.txt`. Then you run `.runtests.py` script, which runs all tests, using `tox` and `pytest`.

