I applied that idea--see the latest commit.  It needed to be a *little* more complicated, because intrinsic_t<ret_type> can be void, but it appears to work.  It's also not *quite* as robust as the template version (each cache variable was local to each instance and method there; with this approach, each cache variable is local to each method, but shared across instances), but it is also much easier to use.

It's still fragile, but it requires a bit less innocuous code:
```C++
class A {
    std::string join_names(B &b1, B &b2) { return b1.name() + b2.name(); }
};
```
but that's definitely much less of a limitation than before.

